ory and in practice of the parameters of human nature and the responsibilities attendant upon the human role.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthority. 0aCommon good. 0aPower (Philosophy) 0aPower (Philosophy). 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845842740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438458427423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438458427/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles